The Sabine farm was situated in the valley of Ustica, thirty miles from Rome, and twelve miles from Tivoli. It possessed the attraction‚ no small one to Horace, of being very secluded—-Varia (Vico Varo), the nearest town, being four miles off—yet, at the same time, within an easy distance of Rome.
